column1: What will the closing price of the Brazilian real-to-US dollar exchange rate be on 15 June 2018?
column11: This question will be resolved using the closing price reported by Bloomberg for 15 June 2018. Confused? Check our FAQ or ask us for help.

column6: Currently Bloomberg is showing 3.7083. Central Bank and others pushed rate down from 3.9657 to that number over the past business week. But a new poll showing lack of trust and impopularity of current government (3%) will likely make it tough for the Central Bank to push rate below 3.6000 by end of trading in Sampa on Friday.
At 3.89 today and has been steadily climbing since February

Bloomies reported Goldman-Sachs experts in April predicting 'big jump' in value of Real aginst US Dollar suggesting that, right around now the rate would be in the area of 3.33 Reals to 1.00 USD. The rate this morning was 3.77 to 1.00 and Central Bank has been spending to prop it up.
